	<!-- The shootings -->
	<!-- 
		The number of max shootings will depend on the max number of enemies possible simultaneously in the scene (50 by default)
		and the max number of simultaneously shootings per enemy in the scene (50 by default), 
		max the max number of them used in the battleship (100 by default). So total = (50 + 1) * 50 = 2550 (by default) 
		All these variables are defined at bsdatagame.hpp / cpp. If those are changed, these ones should do too. 
		The hole for shootings is prepared up to a maximum of 1100 (10 enemies). 
		
		--------------
		CONFIGURATION:
		--------------
		
		To consider more number of shootings:
		1.-	Change the variable _maxNumberOfShootingsPerEnemyInScene defined in the DataGame structure. 
		2.-	Change the number below using the formula (1 + _maxNumberOfEnemiesInScene) * _maxNumberOfShootingsPerEnemyInScene
		3.-	Go to the file bsmovements.xml and change (with the same formula) the number of movements for shootings.
			
		To considerer new types of shooting:
		1.-	Add a new form.
		2.-	Add a new animation for the new form just before the one representing the explosion of the shooting,
			and with the next id to the previous.
		3.-	Change the id of the animation for the explosion.
		4.-	Add a new state for the new type of shooting considering the new animation created and just 
			before the state for the explosion that is common for all types of shooting.
		5.-	Change the id of the state defined for the explosion.
		6.-	Last not least, change the variable _numberOfShootingTypes defined in the structure DataGame.
	-->
